==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pharos
<hw>Pha"ros</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>fa`ros</grk>, fr. <grk>Fa`ros</grk> an island in the Bay of
Alexandria, where king <person>Ptolemy Philadelphus</person> built a
famous lighthouse, one of the seven wonders of the ancient world.]</ety>
<def>A lighthouse or beacon for the guidance of seamen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He . . . built a <qex>pharos</qex>, or lighthouse.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pharyngal</ent>⟦br⟧
